      "writtenOn": "2016-02-24T23:10:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah I think that\u0027s probably a good idea now that I think about it. In that case I would also like to have kUnknownInitError returned if the user passes in an empty string. The scenario I\u0027m thinking about is when you have code like this:\nandroid_init_error_set(13, getErrorStr());\nand getErrorStr() returns an empty string or null. In those cases the error dialog we show would have no text at all and that would be hard to debug and pretty useless to the user. I was thinking that in the null case a default message might be good but now that I think about it it should probably be there for empty strings as well.",
