        "id": 1087048
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-02-24T23:10:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Since internally the string is stored in an std::string there is no way to determine if a null pointer was passed to the set function or an empty string. One approach would be to store a flag that keeps track of this but it seems a little overkill. Another approach might be to treat an empty string the same way as a null string and instead store the default message. Or just store the empty string I guess but the way the code is written right now that would be a very boring error message. I think I\u0027d rather have the default message in that case. Which actually reminds me that I forgot to write a test for that.",
      "parentUuid": "a29b218c_b1ceb5ce",
